Class WMTSParamsPanel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • org.gvsig.raster.wmts.swing.WmtsGUI
              • org.gvsig.raster.wmts.swing.impl.wizard.WMTSParamsPanel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ActionListener, ItemListener, KeyListener, MouseListener, ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable, EventListener, Accessible, ListSelectionListener, TreeSelectionListener

    public class WMTSParamsPanel
extends WmtsGUI
implements ActionListener, ItemListener, KeyListener, ListSelectionListener, MouseListener, TreeSelectionListener
    This class implements the map option panel. It includes a set of Listeners that implement some control rules which refresh the component values that depends on those selected in the other components to avoid to choose an invalid set of options. It also includes a method (isCorrectlyConfigured()) that checks if the current set of values is enough to correctly launch a GetMap request. The information is obtained from a WMTSWizardDataSource object.
